const e={de:{"search-groups":"Gruppen durchsuchen...",groups:"Gruppen","places-description":"Hier sind einige Ideen, wo du gesellig sein kannst.","swiss-tips-description":"Tips & Tricks fÃ¼r das Leben in Bern und in der Schweiz. Diese Tipps sind hauptsÃ¤chlich fÃ¼r NeuankÃ¶mmlinge gedacht und kÃ¶nnen auch fÃ¼r Reisende und Einheimische hilfreich sein, die vielleicht noch nicht von dem einen oder anderen gehÃ¶rt haben.","events-description":"Diese Events sind anders als gewÃ¶hnliche Veranstaltungen. WÃ¤hrend regulÃ¤re Events sich auf das Thema konzentrieren und Menschen oft mit ihrer Gruppe kommen, haben diese Events einen Fokus darauf, neue Leute kennenzulernen. Dies sind Orte, die sich bewusster darum bemÃ¼hen, Menschen zusammenzubringen und eine offenere, einladende AtmosphÃ¤re haben.","logo-description":"Ein Raum zum Verbinden",description:"<strong>Ein physischer und digitaler Ort um sich in Bern zu vernetzen</strong>","groups-description":'In diesen Gruppen findet man verschiedenste AktivitÃ¤ten und Leute. Falls du eine Frage hast, kannst du gerne in der <a href="/groups/connect-bern" title="Connect Bern main group">Connect Bern</a> Gruppe nachfragen.',"map-title":"Digitale Karte","map-description":"Unser digitaler Raum zum Verbinden - sag Hallo zu allen, die auch da sind! Kollaboriere, arbeite, lerne neue Leute kennen oder entspanne einfach.","map-feature-1-title":"Sag Hallo","map-feature-1-desc":"Triff dich mit anderen auf der Karte und tausche dich aus.","map-feature-2-title":"Kollaboriere","map-feature-2-desc":"Arbeite zusammen an Projekten oder organisiere Events.","map-feature-3-title":"Arbeite","map-feature-3-desc":"Nutze den Raum zum Arbeiten und Lernen.","map-feature-4-title":"Entspanne","map-feature-4-desc":"Chill einfach und genieÃŸe die Gemeinschaft.","map-feature-5-title":"Projekt helfen","map-feature-5-desc":"Hilf beim Projekt mit und verbinde dich mit anderen.","map-feature-6-title":"Fragen stellen","map-feature-6-desc":"Hast du Fragen? Komm vorbei und finde jemanden, der dir hilft.","go-to-map":"Geh zur Karte","location-title":"Physischer Raum","location-description":"Ein gemÃ¼tlicher Raum in Bern mit dem alleinigen Zweck, neue Leute zu treffen und Menschen miteinander zu verbinden. Komm vorbei und triff deine Nachbarn in Bern.","location-ideas-title":"Was du bei uns machen kannst:","location-ideas":["ğŸ–¥ï¸ Co-working und andere Leute treffen","ğŸ´ Zum Mittagessen vorbeikommen (bring dein Essen mit)","ğŸ’¬ Komm und plaudere","ğŸ² Bring ein Kartenspiel und finde Leute zum Spielen","ğŸ’¡ Alles andere, was du gerne mit Menschen machst!"],"location-phone":"+41 78 316 67 27","location-contact-intro":"<strong>WhatsApp bevorzugt</strong> - wir antworten schneller!<br/> Kannst du auch anrufen, wenn es dringend ist.","location-volunteers":"Wir arbeiten freiwillig - bitte hab Geduld mit unseren Antwortzeiten! â¤ï¸","location-btn-whatsapp":"ğŸ’¬ WhatsApp","location-btn-call":"ğŸ“ Anrufen","location-call-first":"âš ï¸ <strong>Wichtig:</strong> Schreib uns oder ruf uns zuerst an, komm nicht einfach das erste Mal unangemeldet vorbei, weil vielleicht niemand da ist. Oder, wenn du abenteuerlustig bist, tritt <a href='/map'>der Karte</a> bei und schau, ob jemand zu Hause ist!","location-process":"ğŸ  <strong>Prozess:</strong> WhatsApp-Anruf â†’ Formular ausfÃ¼llen â†’ Willkommensgruppe beitreten â†’ Jemand bestÃ¤tigt den Termin","location-whatsapp-message":"Hi, ich wÃ¼rde gerne das Connect Bern Projekt besuchen!","location-visit-info":`â˜• Komm zu <a href='/events/coffee-cake-connect'><strong>"Coffee, Cake & Connect"</strong></a> jeden Sonntag um 16:00 Uhr - unsere wÃ¶chentliche Zeit, die speziell fÃ¼r neue Leute gedacht ist, die das Projekt kennenlernen mÃ¶chten!`,"about-title":"Ãœber Connect Bern","about-highlight":"Ein Raum in Bern, der sich der echten menschlichen Verbindung widmet, wo das Treffen und Sprechen mit neuen Menschen nicht unangenehm ist, sondern der Sinn dahinter.","about-p1":"Connect Bern ist fÃ¼r Menschen, die neue Leute kennenlernen und ihren Freundeskreis erweitern mÃ¶chten.","about-p1b":"Die meisten Veranstaltungen in der heutigen Gesellschaft konzentrieren sich auf das eigentliche Thema und verpassen einen sehr wichtigen Aspekt - neue Leute kennenzulernen. Die meisten Menschen gehen mit ihren Freunden zu Veranstaltungen, aber was ist, wenn du neue Leute kennenlernen mÃ¶chtest - warum ist es nicht sozial normal und warum fÃ¼hlt es sich so unangenehm an?","about-p2":"Besonders in der Schweiz, in Europa und generell in der westlichen Gesellschaft ist es schwieriger, neue Leute kennenzulernen und neue Freunde zu finden.","about-p3":"Wir sind uns bewusst, dass es viele gute GrÃ¼nde gibt, warum das schwierig ist - aber wir wollen nicht aufgeben, lasst uns das gemeinsam angehen!","what-we-do-title":"Wie wir das erreichen:","what-we-do-physical-title":"Physischer Raum","what-we-do-physical-desc":"Unser Raum ist tagsÃ¼ber geÃ¶ffnet, damit Menschen vorbeikommen, andere treffen und sich austauschen kÃ¶nnen. Ein Ort ohne Druck, einfach da zu sein und echte Verbindungen zu knÃ¼pfen.","what-we-do-digital-title":"Digitaler Raum","what-we-do-digital-desc":"Unsere digitale Karte ist eine Online-Initiative, um Menschen in Bern zusammenzubringen. Auch wenn es online beginnt, kÃ¶nnen sich die Leute spÃ¤ter persÃ¶nlich treffen!","what-we-do-groups-title":"Community-Gruppen","what-we-do-groups-desc":"Wir sammeln und kuratieren themenbezogene Gruppen - sowohl unsere eigenen als auch bestehende Gruppen - und heben die aktiveren und sozialeren hervor, bei denen es wirklich ums Verbinden geht. Wir mÃ¶chten, dass mehr Menschen diese Gemeinschaften entdecken.","what-we-do-events-title":"Veranstaltungen","what-we-do-events-desc":"Ein Ort, um Events zu finden, bei denen es wirklich darum geht, Menschen zu treffen - nicht nur allgemeine Veranstaltungen. Wir organisieren einige selbst und sammeln andere, die wir kennen. Wenn du von einem Event weisst, teile es gerne mit uns!","what-we-do-tips-title":"Sonstiges","what-we-do-tips-desc":"Ein bisschen Hilfe hier und da - zum Beispiel Schweizer Tipps und andere nÃ¼tzliche Informationen, damit Menschen die schÃ¶nen Dinge finden kÃ¶nnen, die es gibt.","what-we-do-places-title":"Soziale Orte","what-we-do-places-desc":"Eine kleine Liste wirklich sozialer Orte - nicht zu kommerziell, fokussiert auf Gemeinschaft, mit vielen Events. Orte, wo man auch einfach dasitzen kann, ohne etwas konsumieren zu mÃ¼ssen. Wir zeigen, was existiert!","about-values-title":"Was uns wichtig ist:","about-safe-space-title":"Sicherer Raum","about-safe-space-desc":"Sicherer Raum fÃ¼r Minderheiten - wir mÃ¶chten, dass sich Familien, die Ã¤ltere Generation, LGBTQ+, Personen aus dem Ausland und Frauen in unseren RÃ¤umen und bei den von uns organisierten Veranstaltungen sicher fÃ¼hlen. Wir arbeiten aktiv daran, dies zu erreichen und freuen uns sehr Ã¼ber VorschlÃ¤ge, wie wir uns verbessern kÃ¶nnen.","about-positive-title":"Positiv bleiben","about-positive-desc":"Wir bemÃ¼hen uns, eine positive und einladende Umgebung fÃ¼r echte Verbindungen zu schaffen! Wir heissen Menschen herzlich willkommen, die ihren Freundeskreis erweitern mÃ¶chten, mÃ¶chten aber transparent sein, dass wir nicht fÃ¼r psychische GesundheitsunterstÃ¼tzung ausgestattet sind. Wenn du mit ernsthafter Einsamkeit oder Depression zu kÃ¤mpfen hast, ermutigen wir dich, professionelle Hilfe zu suchen - wir kÃ¶nnen Teil deines UnterstÃ¼tzungsnetzwerks sein, aber kein Ersatz fÃ¼r professionelle Betreuung.","about-hygiene-title":"PersÃ¶nlicher Raum","about-hygiene-desc":"Komm nicht kÃ¶rperlich zu nah an andere heran, respektiere ihren persÃ¶nlichen Raum, versuche achtsam zu sein, ob deine NÃ¤he sie unwohl fÃ¼hlen lÃ¤sst - sei es, weil sie es einfach nicht mÃ¶gen, Menschen physisch so nah zu sein, oder vielleicht wegen eines Geruchs. Versuchen wir, das Bewusstsein dafÃ¼r zu schÃ¤rfen!","about-boundaries-title":"Grenzen respektieren","about-boundaries-desc":"Dies ist ein Ort, um Menschen zu treffen, und die Grenze zwischen Plaudern, Extrovertiertheit, Versuchen ein GesprÃ¤ch aufrechtzuerhalten und Aufdringlichkeit ist sehr fein. Versuchen wir alle, uns dessen bewusst zu sein, versuchen wir, einander nicht zu verurteilen und gemeinsam zu lernen, wie man sanft zur nÃ¤chsten Person Ã¼bergeht. Denk daran, Menschen zu finden, mit denen du wirklich eine Verbindung hast, ist keine leichte Aufgabe und du musst vielleicht ein paar Mal vorbeikommen, bis du endlich deine Leute findest.","about-no-dating-title":"Kein Dating-Ort","about-no-dating-desc":"Dies ist kein Ort, um Frauen anzubaggern. Leider passiert es in Ã¶ffentlich zugÃ¤nglichen RÃ¤umen, wo es weniger soziale Verantwortlichkeit gibt, dass viele MÃ¤nner das versuchen, aber wir tolerieren das Ã¼berhaupt nicht. Wenn dich jemand unwohl fÃ¼hlen lÃ¤sst, bring das Thema bitte zur Sprache, wenn du dich wohl genug fÃ¼hlst - wir werden dich unterstÃ¼tzen. Dies beinhaltet das Senden privater Nachrichten oder jegliche Art von unangemessenem Verhalten. Der Fokus auf Dating verdirbt es wirklich fÃ¼r die Frauen, sie werden bereits Ã¼berall sonst im Leben angemacht, lasst uns dies zu einem sicheren Raum fÃ¼r sie machen.","about-active-title":"Aktiv & Entwickelnd","about-active-desc":"Dieses Ziel zu erreichen ist extrem herausfordernd. Wir kÃ¤mpfen stÃ¤ndig damit, die Erwartungen zwischen verschiedenen Arten von Menschen in Einklang zu bringen, wir machen Fehler, lernen und wachsen. Aber wir wollen nicht aufgeben! Wir suchen Hilfe, sei es finanziell oder einfach durch deine Zeit als freiwillige Person. Bitte melde dich bei uns, um uns RatschlÃ¤ge zu geben, deine Meinung zu teilen, wir sind daran interessiert, besser zu werden! Wir haben auch reine Frauengruppen, falls du daran interessiert bist, dort beizutreten und zu teilen :)","support-us-title":"Wie kann ich helfen?","support-us-description":"Es gibt viele MÃ¶glichkeiten, wie du uns helfen kannst, unsere Vision zu erreichen, Menschen in Bern zu verbinden. Hier sind einige davon, vielen Dank fÃ¼rs Lesen!","support-share-title":"ğŸ“¢ Sag es weiter!","support-share-desc":"Die beste Art, uns zu helfen, ist uns bekannt zu machen! Schreib direkt eine Nachricht an deine Freunde und Bekannten in Bern, folge unserem <a href='https://instagram.com/connect.bern' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Instagram</a>, teile unsere <a href='https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1hUOX6YvN8inSiIDnKmFIfYXhWcI0h8Fn?usp=sharing' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Flyer</a> auf Instagram oder anderen sozialen Medien oder bring neue Leute zu unserem Ort oder zu unseren Events! Jede neue Person, die von uns hÃ¶rt, hilft uns, die Gemeinschaft wachsen zu lassen und lebendig zu halten!","support-events-title":"ğŸ¯ Hilf bei der Planung von Events","support-events-desc":"Wir haben einen Raum, um Events zu kreieren, die Menschen zusammenbringen und echte Verbindungen schaffen, und wir brauchen deine Hilfe dabei! Besuche unsere <a href='https://github.com/connectbern/events/issues' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>GitHub Event-Issues-Seite</a> um Kommentare zu schreiben, Tipps zu geben, Ideen beizutragen oder eine vÃ¶llig neue Event-Idee hinzuzufÃ¼gen!","support-physical-title":"ğŸ¤ Hilf bei Events vor Ort","support-physical-desc":"Du kannst auch bei Events selbst helfen: komm frÃ¼her und hilf beim Aufbauen, bleib etwas lÃ¤nger zum AufrÃ¤umen, hilf beim Empfang neuer Leute, teile Ideen wie wir Dinge verbessern kÃ¶nnen. Schon allein dein Interesse am Helfen zu zeigen, hilft sehr! Es ist enorm hilfreich, wenn wir Menschen dabei haben, die sich Zeit genommen haben, die Mission und die Vision des Projekts zu verstehen.","support-financial-title":"ğŸ’ Finanzielle UnterstÃ¼tzung","support-financial-desc":"Die Miete ist teuer - das ist der Hauptgrund, warum wir Geld brauchen. Wir haben einen zentralen Ort in Bern mit einem groÃŸartigen Vermieter und keine Probleme mit den Nachbarn, und wir wÃ¼rden ihn sehr gerne behalten! Wenn du Ideen hast, wie du das Projekt finanziell unterstÃ¼tzen kannst, wÃ¼rden wir das gerne hÃ¶ren.","support-donations-title":"Wenn du in der Lage bist und daran interessiert bist zu spenden, so geht's!","support-donations-intro":"Finanzielle UnterstÃ¼tzung ist entscheidend fÃ¼r unser Fortbestehen. Ohne regelmÃ¤ssige Spenden kÃ¶nnen wir diesen Raum nicht offen halten. Wenn du in der Lage bist und daran interessiert bist zu spenden, oder jemanden kennst, der uns unterstÃ¼tzen kÃ¶nnte, wÃ¼rden wir das unglaublich schÃ¤tzen. Jeder Beitrag macht einen echten Unterschied. ğŸ’™","support-membership-core-title":"Kernteam-Mitgliedschaft","support-membership-core-desc":"Wenn du in der Schweiz arbeitest und es dir leisten kannst, ist dies ein hilfreicher Betrag. Du hilfst uns, den Raum am Laufen zu halten und wirst ein wichtiger Teil unserer Gemeinschaft. Sieh es als Ersatz fÃ¼r deinen Co-Working-Platz!","support-membership-regular-title":"RegelmÃ¤ssige Mitgliedschaft","support-membership-regular-desc":"Perfekt fÃ¼r alle, die ab und zu vorbeikommen und das Projekt unterstÃ¼tzen mÃ¶chten. Wenn du in der Schweiz arbeitest und es dir leisten kannst, ist dies eine schÃ¶ne Spende, die uns hilft, diesen besonderen Ort fÃ¼r alle offen zu halten.","support-alpian-title":"ğŸ Wir haben einen kreativen Weg gefunden: Wir bekommen 100 CHF, du bekommst 75 CHF - alle gewinnen!","support-alpian-desc":"Mit Alpian kannst du uns helfen, 100 CHF zu bekommen, <strong>ohne einen Rappen zu bezahlen!</strong> ErÃ¶ffne einfach ein kostenloses Alpian-Konto mit unserem Code <strong>PCC7HH</strong> und zahle 500 CHF ein. Alpian gibt uns automatisch 100 CHF und <strong>DU bekommst 75 CHF geschenkt!</strong>","support-creative-title":"ğŸ’¡ Hast du kreative Ideen?","support-creative-desc":"Wir suchen immer nach neuen, kreativen Wegen, um das Projekt zu finanzieren! Hast du Ideen, oder kannst du oder jemand, den du kennst, uns mit den bestehenden Ideen helfen?","support-creative-ideas-title":"Zum Beispiel:","support-creative-idea-1":"ğŸ“… <strong>Miete den Raum fÃ¼r Events</strong> - Kennst du ein Unternehmen oder eine Organisation, die einen Raum braucht? Perfekt fÃ¼r Workshops, Meetings oder private Veranstaltungen","support-creative-idea-2":"ğŸ¤ <strong>Sponsoring-MÃ¶glichkeiten</strong> - Kennst du Unternehmen, die soziale Projekte unterstÃ¼tzen?","support-creative-idea-3":"ğŸ“ <strong>Grants & FÃ¶rdergelder</strong> - Kennst du Programme? Wir kennen bereits Migros Kultur. Oder vielleicht hast du Erfahrung mit FÃ¶rderantrÃ¤gen oder kennst jemanden, der sich damit auskennt?","support-creative-idea-4":"ğŸ’­ <strong>Teile deine Ideen</strong> - Kennst du andere Ideen, wie wir uns finanzieren kÃ¶nnten?","support-btn-contact-ideas":"ğŸ’¬ Kontaktiere uns mit deinen Ideen","support-alpian-code":"Empfehlungscode:","support-alpian-code-value":"PCC7HH","support-alpian-steps-title":"So funktioniert's:","support-alpian-step-1":"Lade die Alpian App herunter und registriere dich","support-alpian-step-2":"Verwende unseren Code <strong>PCC7HH</strong> bei der Anmeldung","support-alpian-step-3":"Lade 500 CHF auf dein Konto auf","support-alpian-step-4":"Wir bekommen 100 CHF","support-alpian-step-5":"Du bekommst 75 CHF","support-btn-alpian-app":"ğŸ“± Jetzt Alpian App herunterladen und uns helfen","support-btn-copy-code":"Code kopieren","support-donate-title":"Einmalige Spende","support-donate-desc":"Du kannst auch einfach spenden, was du kannst:","support-donate-per-event":"ğŸ’ Empfohlene Spende pro Event: <strong>CHF 20</strong>","support-donate-per-event-desc":"Jeder ist willkommen â€“ auch wenn du kein Geld spenden kannst. Wir glauben daran, Menschen zusammenzubringen, unabhÃ¤ngig von ihrer finanziellen Situation. Wenn du in der Schweiz arbeitest, ist CHF 20 eine nette Spende, die uns hilft, die Kosten fÃ¼r Essen, GetrÃ¤nke, Miete und Organisation zu decken. Wenn du nicht finanziell beitragen kannst, kannst du gerne deine Zeit als Freiwillige/r einbringen!","support-ways-to-donate":"Zahlungsmethoden:","support-twint-title":"ğŸ“± Twint","support-twint-desc":"Der einfachste Weg zu spenden mit deinem Handy:","support-twint-note":"FÃ¼r kleinere BetrÃ¤ge bevorzugen wir, dass du direkt an unsere Nummer twintest, um die hohe GebÃ¼hr von Twint zu vermeiden.","support-twint-number":"Unsere Twint-Nummer:","support-twint-number-value":"+41 78 316 67 27","support-btn-save-contact":"ğŸ“ Kontakt speichern","support-btn-copy-number":"Nummer kopieren","support-credit-card-title":"ğŸ’³ Kreditkarte","support-credit-card-desc":"Spende sicher online mit deiner Kredit- oder Debitkarte:","support-btn-credit-card":"Kreditkarte","support-bank-title":"ğŸ¦ BankÃ¼berweisung (eBanking)","support-bank-desc":"Du kannst eine direkte Ãœberweisung auf unser Konto machen. Bitte kontaktiere uns fÃ¼r IBAN-Nummer und Details.","support-bank-holder":"Kontoinhaber:","support-bank-holder-value":"Chagai Friedlander","support-bank-iban":"IBAN:","support-bank-iban-value":"CH4108440258673882001","support-bank-name":"Bank:","support-bank-name-value":"Cler","support-bank-reference":"Verwendungszweck:","support-bank-reference-value":"Spende - Connect Bern","support-cash-title":"ğŸ’µ Bargeld","support-cash-desc":"Bevorzugst du persÃ¶nlich zu spenden? Bargeldspenden sind immer willkommen!","support-cash-details":"Du kannst deine Spende in der dafÃ¼r vorgesehenen Box in unserem Raum hinterlassen. Suche nach der Spendenbox in der NÃ¤he des Eingangs.","support-thank-you":"Danke, dass du unsere Gemeinschaft unterstÃ¼tzt! ğŸ™","support-thank-you-desc":"Jeder Beitrag hilft uns, diesen Raum offen und einladend fÃ¼r alle zu halten.","contact-title":"Schreib uns","contact-description":"Hast du eine Frage, einen Vorschlag oder mÃ¶chtest du dich einfach melden?<br>FÃ¼lle das untenstehende Formular aus und wir melden uns so schnell wie mÃ¶glich bei dir!","contact-name":"Name","contact-email":"E-Mail *","contact-phone":"Telefonnummer","contact-message":"Nachricht","contact-submit":"Nachricht senden","contact-submitting":"Wird gesendet...","contact-success":"Vielen Dank! Wir melden uns bald bei dir.","contact-error":"Etwas ist schiefgelaufen. Bitte versuche es erneut.","events-suggest-title":"Weisst du von einem Event?","events-suggest-description":"Wir suchen Events, die sich auf das Kennenlernen neuer Menschen konzentrieren â€“ nicht nur kommerzielle oder thematisch fokussierte Veranstaltungen. Wenn das Event, von dem du weisst, Menschen zusammenbringt und eine offene, einladende AtmosphÃ¤re schafft, wÃ¼rden wir gerne davon hÃ¶ren!","events-suggest-button":"Event vorschlagen","events-why-different":"Warum sind diese Events anders?","events-why-different-title":"Was macht diese Events besonders?"},en:{"search-groups":"Search groups...",groups:"Groups","swiss-tips-description":"Tips & Tricks for living in Bern and Switzerland! These tips are mainly for newcomers and might also be helpful for travelers and locals who might not have heard about a thing or two.","places-description":"Here are some ideas of where you can be social.","events-description":"These events are different from regular events. While regular events focus on the topic itself and people often come with their group, these events have a focus on meeting new people. These are places that are more conscious about bringing people together and have a more open, welcoming atmosphere.","logo-description":"A space to connect",description:"<strong>A physical and digital space to connect in Bern</strong>","groups-description":'In these groups you can do many different things. If you have a general question, feel free to ask in the <a href="/groups/connect-bern" title="Connect Bern main group">Connect Bern</a> group. People will be happy to help out.',"map-title":"Digital Map","map-description":"Our digital space to connect - say hi to anyone who's also there! Collaborate, work, meet people, or just chill.","map-feature-1-title":"Say Hi","map-feature-1-desc":"Meet up with others on the map and connect.","map-feature-2-title":"Collaborate","map-feature-2-desc":"Work together on projects or organize events.","map-feature-3-title":"Work","map-feature-3-desc":"Use the space for working and learning.","map-feature-4-title":"Chill","map-feature-4-desc":"Just relax and enjoy the community.","map-feature-5-title":"Help the Project","map-feature-5-desc":"Help with the project and connect with people.","map-feature-6-title":"Ask Questions","map-feature-6-desc":"Have questions about anything? Join and find someone to help you.","go-to-map":"Go to the Map","location-title":"Physical Space","location-description":"A comfy space in Bern with the sole purpose of meeting new people and connecting between people. Come visit and meet your neighbors in Bern.","location-ideas-title":"What you can do at our place:","location-ideas":["ğŸ–¥ï¸ Co-work and meet other people working","ğŸ´ Join for lunch (bring your lunch with you)","ğŸ’¬ Come and chat","ğŸ² Bring a card game and find people to play","ğŸ’¡ Anything else you like doing with people!"],"location-phone":"+41 78 316 67 27","location-contact-intro":"<strong>WhatsApp preferred</strong> - we respond faster!<br/> You can also call if it's urgent.","location-volunteers":"We're volunteers - please be patient with our response times! â¤ï¸","location-btn-whatsapp":"ğŸ’¬ WhatsApp","location-btn-call":"ğŸ“ Call","location-call-first":"âš ï¸ <strong>Important:</strong> Write us or call us first, don't just show up the first time unanounced because there might not be anyone there. Or, if you're feeling adventurous, join <a href='/map'>the map</a> and check if anyone is home!","location-process":"ğŸ  <strong>Process:</strong> WhatsApp call â†’ Fill form â†’ Join welcome group â†’ Someone confirms they can show you around","location-whatsapp-message":"Hi, I would love to visit the Connect Bern project!","location-visit-info":`â˜• Come to <a href='/events/coffee-cake-connect'><strong>"Coffee, Cake & Connect"</strong></a> every Sunday at 4pm - our weekly time dedicated for new people who want to see what the project is about!`,"about-title":"About Connect Bern","about-highlight":"A space in Bern dedicated to genuine human connection, where meeting and talking to new people isn't awkward, it's the point.","about-p1":"Connect Bern is for people looking to meet new people and expand their friend circle.","about-p1b":"Most events in society nowadays are concentrated on the actual topic, missing a very important aspect - meeting new people. Most people go to events together with their friends, but what if you want to meet new people - why is it not socially normal and why does it feel so awkward?","about-p2":"Especially in Switzerland, in Europe and in general in western society it is more difficult to meet new people and to make new friends.","about-p3":"We are aware that there are many good reasons why this is difficult - but we don't want to give up, let's tackle this together!","what-we-do-title":"How We Achieve This:","what-we-do-physical-title":"Physical Space","what-we-do-physical-desc":"Our space is open during the day for anyone to come, meet people, and socialize. A place with no pressure, just to be present and make genuine connections.","what-we-do-digital-title":"Digital Space","what-we-do-digital-desc":"Our digital map is an online initiative to bring people together in Bern. Even if it starts online, people can meet physically later on!","what-we-do-groups-title":"Community Groups","what-we-do-groups-desc":"We gather and curate topic-specific groups - both our own and existing ones - and highlight the more active and social ones that are really about connecting. We want more people to discover these communities.","what-we-do-events-title":"Events","what-we-do-events-desc":"A place to find events that are truly about meeting people - not just general events. We organize some ourselves and gather others we know about. If you know of an event, please share it with us!","what-we-do-tips-title":"Other Things","what-we-do-tips-desc":"A little help here and there - for example Swiss tips and other useful information - so people can find the nice things that exist.","what-we-do-places-title":"Social Places","what-we-do-places-desc":"A small list of truly social places - not too commercial, focused on community, with lots of events. Places where you can just sit without having to consume anything. We're showing what exists!","about-values-title":"Things that are important to us:","about-safe-space-title":"Safe Space","about-safe-space-desc":"Safe space for minority groups - we want families, the older generation, LGBTQ+, foreigners and women to feel safe in the spaces that we have and the events that we organize. We actively work on trying to achieve that and we are more than happy for suggestions on how to improve.","about-positive-title":"Stay Positive","about-positive-desc":"We strive to create a positive and welcoming environment for making genuine connections! While we warmly welcome people looking to expand their social circle, we want to be transparent that we're not equipped to provide mental health support. If you're dealing with serious loneliness or depression, we encourage seeking professional help - we can be part of your support network, but not a replacement for professional care.","about-hygiene-title":"Personal Space","about-hygiene-desc":"Don't get too physically close to people, respect their personal space, try to be more aware if how close you are makes them feel uncomfortable - be it because they just don't like being so close to people physically or perhaps because of some odor, whether we just ate some garlic, we had to run to the bus and now we sweat, or because we smoke. Let's try to raise awareness for that!","about-boundaries-title":"Respect Boundaries","about-boundaries-desc":"This is a place to meet people and the line between chatting, being an extrovert, trying to keep up a conversation and being pushy is very fine. Let's all try to be aware of that, try not to judge each other and learn together how to continue to the next person gently. Remember, finding people you really connect with is no easy task and you might need to come a few times until you finally find your peeps.","about-no-dating-title":"Not a Dating Scene","about-no-dating-desc":"This is not a place to pick up girls. Unfortunately, in spaces open to the public, where there is less social accountability, a lot of guys attempt this, but we do not tolerate this at all. If someone makes you feel uncomfortable, please bring up the topic if you're comfortable doing so - we will support you. This includes sending private messages or any kind of inappropriate behavior. Focusing on dating really ruins it for the girls, women are already getting hit on everywhere else in life, let's keep this a safe space for them.","about-active-title":"Active & Evolving","about-active-desc":"Trying to achieve this goal is extremely challenging. We are constantly struggling with how to align expectations between different types of people, we are making mistakes, learning and growing. But we don't want to give up! We are looking for help, be it financially or just volunteering your time. Please reach out to us, to give us advice, your opinion, we are interested in getting better! We also have a women only groups if you're interested in joining that and sharing there :)","support-us-title":"How can I help?","support-us-description":"There are many ways you can help us achieve our vision of connecting people in Bern, here are a few of them, thanks so much for reading!","support-share-title":"ğŸ“¢ Spread the word!","support-share-desc":"The best way to help us is to spread the word! Write a message directly to your friends and acquaintances in Bern, follow our <a href='https://instagram.com/connect.bern' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>Instagram</a>, share our <a href='https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1hUOX6YvN8inSiIDnKmFIfYXhWcI0h8Fn?usp=sharing' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>flyers</a> on Instagram or other social media, or bring new people to our place or events! Every new person who hears about us, helps us to grow the community and keep it alive!","support-events-title":"ğŸ¯ Help With Event Planning","support-events-desc":"We have a space to create events that bring people together and foster genuine connections, and we need your help making that happen! Visit our <a href='https://github.com/connectbern/events/issues' target='_blank' rel='noopener noreferrer'>GitHub event issues page</a> to write comments, give tips, contribute ideas, or add a completely new event idea!","support-physical-title":"ğŸ¤ Help At Events","support-physical-desc":"You can also help at the events themselves: come early and help with organizing, stay a bit later to clean up, help welcoming new people, share ideas on how to improve things. Just expressing your interest in helping already goes a long way! It helps enormously when we have people around who have spent some time trying to understand the mission and the vision of the project.","support-financial-title":"ğŸ’ Financial Support","support-financial-desc":"The rent is expensive - that's the main reason we need the money. We have a central place in Bern with a great landlord and no problems with the neighbors, and we'd love to keep it! If you have ideas on how to help the project financially, we'd love to hear them.","support-donations-title":"If you're able and interested in donating, here's how!","support-donations-intro":"Financial support is critical for our survival. Without regular donations, we cannot keep this space open. If you're able and interested in donating, or know someone who could support us, we would incredibly appreciate it. Every contribution makes a real difference. ğŸ’™","support-membership-core-title":"Core Team Membership","support-membership-core-desc":"If you're working in Switzerland and can afford it, this is a helpful amount. You help us keep the space running and become an important part of our community. Think of it as a replacement to your co-working place!","support-membership-regular-title":"Regular Membership","support-membership-regular-desc":"Perfect for those who visit occasionally and want to support the project. If you're working in Switzerland and can afford it, this is a nice donation that helps us keep this special place open for everyone.","support-alpian-title":"ğŸ We found a creative way: We get 100 CHF, you get 75 CHF - everyone wins!","support-alpian-desc":"With Alpian, you can help us get 100 CHF <strong>without paying anything!</strong> Simply open a free Alpian account using our code <strong>PCC7HH</strong> and deposit 500 CHF. Alpian automatically gives us 100 CHF and <strong>YOU get 75 CHF as a gift!</strong>","support-creative-title":"ğŸ’¡ Got creative ideas?","support-creative-desc":"We're always looking for new, creative ways to fund the project! Do you have ideas, or can you or anyone you know help us with the existing ideas?","support-creative-ideas-title":"For example:","support-creative-idea-1":"ğŸ“… <strong>Rent the space for events</strong> - Do you know of a company or organisation that needs a space? Perfect for workshops, meetings, or private gatherings","support-creative-idea-2":"ğŸ¤ <strong>Sponsorship opportunities</strong> - Know any companies that support social projects?","support-creative-idea-3":"ğŸ“ <strong>Grants & Funding Programs</strong> - Do you know of any programs? We're already aware of Migros Kultur. Or perhaps you have experience with grant applications or know someone who could help us?","support-creative-idea-4":"ğŸ’­ <strong>Share your ideas</strong> - Do you know of any other ideas of how we could fund ourselves?","support-btn-contact-ideas":"ğŸ’¬ Contact us with your ideas","support-alpian-code":"Referral Code:","support-alpian-code-value":"PCC7HH","support-alpian-steps-title":"How it works:","support-alpian-step-1":"Download the Alpian app and register","support-alpian-step-2":"Use our code <strong>PCC7HH</strong> when signing up","support-alpian-step-3":"Top up your account with 500 CHF","support-alpian-step-4":"We get 100 CHF","support-alpian-step-5":"You get 75 CHF","support-btn-alpian-app":"ğŸ“± Download Alpian App now and help us","support-btn-copy-code":"Copy Code","support-donate-title":"One-Time Donation","support-donate-desc":"You can also just donate whatever you can:","support-donate-per-event":"ğŸ’ Recommended donation per event: <strong>CHF 20</strong>","support-donate-per-event-desc":"Everyone is welcome here â€“ even if you don't have money to donate. We believe in bringing people together regardless of their financial situation. If you're working in Switzerland, CHF 20 is a nice donation that helps us cover the costs of food, drinks, rent, and organization. If you're not able to contribute financially, you're welcome to volunteer your time to help us keep this space running!","support-ways-to-donate":"Payment Methods:","support-twint-title":"ğŸ“± Twint","support-twint-desc":"The easiest way to donate using your mobile phone:","support-twint-note":"For lower amounts we prefer you Twint directly to our number, to avoid the high fee from Twint.","support-twint-number":"Our Twint number:","support-twint-number-value":"+41 78 316 67 27","support-btn-save-contact":"ğŸ“ Save Contact","support-btn-copy-number":"Copy Number","support-credit-card-title":"ğŸ’³ Credit Card","support-credit-card-desc":"Donate securely online with your credit or debit card:","support-btn-credit-card":"Credit Card","support-bank-title":"ğŸ¦ Bank Transfer (eBANKING)","support-bank-desc":"You can make a direct bank transfer to our account. Please contact us for IBAN number and details.","support-bank-holder":"Account Holder:","support-bank-holder-value":"Chagai Friedlander","support-bank-iban":"IBAN:","support-bank-iban-value":"CH4108440258673882001","support-bank-name":"Bank:","support-bank-name-value":"Cler","support-bank-reference":"Reference:","support-bank-reference-value":"Donation - Connect Bern","support-cash-title":"ğŸ’µ Cash","support-cash-desc":"Prefer to donate in person? Cash donations are always welcome!","support-cash-details":"You can leave your donation in the designated box at our space. Look for the donation box near the entrance.","support-thank-you":"Thank you for supporting our community! ğŸ™","support-thank-you-desc":"Every contribution helps us keep this space open and welcoming for everyone.","contact-title":"Get in touch","contact-description":"Have a question, suggestion, or just want to reach out?<br>Fill out the form below and we'll get back to you as soon as possible!","contact-name":"Name","contact-email":"Email *","contact-phone":"Phone Number","contact-message":"Message","contact-submit":"Send Message","contact-submitting":"Sending...","contact-success":"Thank you! We'll get back to you soon.","contact-error":"Something went wrong. Please try again.","events-suggest-title":"Know of an event?","events-suggest-description":"We're looking for events that focus on meeting new people â€“ not just commercial or topic-focused gatherings. If the event you know of brings people together and creates an open, welcoming atmosphere, we'd love to hear about it!","events-suggest-button":"Suggest an Event","events-why-different":"Why are these events different?","events-why-different-title":"What makes these events special?"}};export{e as t};
